  "chunk_index": 41,
  "summary": "Shelley informs Miss Marple and Xie Li that Arthur Badcock is at the police station to assist with an investigation. Xie Li shares a rumor from Mr. Upshaw suggesting that Arthur Badcock was previously married to the actress Marina Gregg before her career became successful. This news makes Miss Marple restless and determined to act. She instructs Miss Knight to call Inspector Englebert and begins searching for a medical book to consult a specific page related to a hint provided by Dr. Haddock.\n\nMiss Marple calls the Reverend to ask about a reception held when Mrs. Badcock died. She inquires if he recalls a conversation between Mrs. Badcock and Miss Gregg regarding a chance encounter in Bermuda. The Reverend remembers Mrs. Badcock mentioning that she had a mild form of measles at that time.\n\nDriven by this information, Miss Marple takes a taxi driven by Roberts to Goose Green House to see Mr. Jason Rad. Upon arrival, she meets a frail, confused man and a polite young man with an American accent named Blackley Preston. Despite Preston's attempts to prevent her from seeing Mr. Rad, Miss Marple insists on waiting. Preston eventually returns with Dr. Gilchrist, a man in tweeds who recognizes Miss Marple through his friendship with Dr. Haddock. Miss Marple maintains her resolve to speak with Mr. Rad.",
